<div class="container" id="features">
  <div class="marketing">
    <h1>Make your crowdsourcing project</h1>

    <div class="row-fluid" style="margin-top: 40px; text-align: left; ">
      <div class="span4">
        <img class="img_feature" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Z%C3%A9ro.svg/100px-Z%C3%A9ro.svg.png"/>
        <h2>minimal setup</h2>
        <p>
          No server. no database. no deployment process. Microapp.io is green and reuses existing web (cloud) services. If you want a community forum, create a Facebook page or a Google group.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="span4">
        <img class="img_feature" src="http://taravana-tdm.com/local/cache-vignettes/L100xH100/rubon52-7ddaa.png" />
        <h2> open app = open code + data</h2>
        <p>
          Microapp.io has an open policy: your data and your code are at any time accessible by anyone (in read-only mode) to facilitate the emergence of best practices.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="span4">
        <img class="img_feature" src="http://www.spraypaintstencils.com/sciencestencils/dna-stencil-thumb.gif">
        <h2>Clone apps</h2>
        <p>
          Anyone can clone existing apps and modify the data or the code to launch their own variant crowdsourcing project in few minutes, or prototype and test different versions
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" style="text-align: left;">
      <div class="span4">
        <img  class="img_feature" src="http://medias.synergeek.fr/2012/01/File-Adobe-Dreamweaver-JavaScript-icon.png" style="filter: url(filters.svg#grayscale);filter: gray;-webkit-filter: grayscale(1);" />
        <h2>One Language: Javascript</h2>
        <p>
          no need of server-side code (python, ruby or php). Only some knowledge HTML(5)/ JS is required. Microapp provides a JS framework based on <a href="http://backbonejs.org/">Backbone.js</a>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="span4">
        <img class="img_feature" src="http://goodsoundonline.net/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/mixcloud_cloud1.jpg">
        <h2>Cloud data</h2>
        <p>
          We use <a href="http://www.google.com/fusiontables">google fusion tables</a> to store your data and not an internal database because anyone can easily view, export, analyze, visualize it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="span4">
        <img  class="img_feature" src="http://qph.cf.quoracdn.net/main-thumb-t-3903-100-CJ0FqiZ57U3GeNELekTTkx3dsZ0BUgXq.jpeg">
        <h2>Cloud coding</h2>
        <p>
          Code online your app via our web editor. Your app is updated on the fly and the code is stored in <a href="https://gist.github.com">Github</a> to manage versionning and faciliate collaboration.
          <!-- By using Gist , we integrate its social coding features in the building of micro-apps e.g. (public code, easy remix/fork, code comments) and facilitate the emergence of eco-system with best practices in micro-tasking. For instance newcomers can easily fork/remix existing micro-apps in few minutes. </p> -->
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row" style="text-align: left;">
      <div class="span4">
        <img class="img_feature" src="http://www.fanastick.com/images/stickers/447/Thumb3.jpg">
        <h2>Workflow design</h2>
        <p>
          Design your own workflow at the user level (e.g. intro, tutorial,test, real task) and at the collective level e.g. iterative or parallel collective problem solving models, or pipeline of apps
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="span4">
        <img  class="img_feature" src="http://shivsingh.com/goingsocial/images/viral.jpg">
        <!-- http://www.supadupawebdesign.co.uk/images/articles/20/captcha.jpg
        -->
        <h2>Embedable app</h2>
        <p>
          Embed your microapp directly on your own web site like a Youtube video <!-- You are responsible to host any further tutorials/doc on your website.-->
          so your visitors can play with the app or embed the app on their websites to support your action beyond traditional advertising or  <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CAPTCHA" target="_blank">captcha</a>.<!-- be creative, you can build custom captcha 'with a purpose' for your website, or active banner you can distribute to your partners' websites instead of advertising. -->
        </p>
      </div>
      <div  class="span4">
        <img class="img_feature" src="http://qph.cf.quoracdn.net/main-thumb-t-2801-100-BBm0YIIqvc8tF4DjNNGuJ8KshjjZSoO8.jpeg">
        <h2>Mechanical Turk compatible</h2>
        <p>
          A layer to make your app compatible with <a href="https://www.mturk.com">Amazon mechanical turk service (AMT)</a> is provided.
        </p>
      </div>
